# References and Attributions



## History

This course was first taught by Michael Musick at the University of Montana in the Fall of 2016.

The online version was first presented during the Fall of 2017.



## Content

This course is modeled from and includes adapted content from [NYU ITP's Introduction to Computational Media](https://github.com/ITPNYU/ICM-2015) & Lady K's (https://github.com/LadyK) Creative Coding Course (https://github.com/IDMNYU/DM-UY-1133-A-CreativeCoding-Bennett/blob/master/README.md) from NYU's IDM.

Many code examples are also copied or derived from examples available from;

- [Getting Started with p5.js](https://www.amazon.com/Make-Interactive-Graphics-JavaScript-Processing/dp/1457186772/)
- [Getting Started with p5.js code](https://github.com/lmccart/gswp5.js-code)
- [Learning Processing code ported to p5.js](https://github.com/shiffman/LearningProcessing-p5.js)
- [Video lesson accompanying code](https://github.com/CodingRainbow/Rainbow-Code/tree/master/p5.js)

Additional material has been linked from or adapted from;

- [scotch.io](https:scotch.io)
- Wikipedia Articles for general information



## Website Template

The course website has been adapted and built from [P2PU.org's](http://howto.p2pu.org), [course-in-a-box](https://github.com/p2pu/course-in-a-box/) and their [Jekyll Course template](http://github.com/p2pu/jekyll-course-template).





## Plugin, Libraries, and Packages

The live reloading and code editing capabilities are capable through the use of [Jotted](https://ghinda.net/jotted/). This creates an "environment for showcasing self-hosted HTML, CSS and JavaScript snippets, with editable source."
